article.headline: Vermont 80, Quinnipiac 72
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Marqus Blakely scored 19 points and Mike Trimboli had 18 as Vermont held off Quinnipiac 80-72 on Saturday night. Quinnipiac's DeMario Anderson hit a layup to pull the Bobcats within 43-42 with 17:19 left in the game, but the Catamounts (4-7) took control with a 14-0 run over the next 3:22 for a 57-42 lead. Quinnipiac (5-6) twice cut Vermont's lead to five, first on DeMario Anderson's two free throws with 2:25 to go that made it 71-66, and again with 28 seconds to play when Karl Anderson's layup made it 77-72. But Vermont held on. DeMario Anderson led the Bobcats with 25 points. Kyle Cieplicki matched a season-high with 16 points for Vermont, while Nick Vier added 12. Blakely had a team-high seven rebounds while Trimboli had a five assists.
